@startuml
actor Student
participant Browser
participant "EduSecure API" as API
participant "AuthService" as Auth
participant "MfaService" as MFA
participant "JwtService" as Jwt
participant "AuthCookieService" as Cookie
database DB

Student -> Browser : enter name, email, password
Browser -> API : POST /api/auth/register over HTTPS
API -> Auth : register(request)
Auth -> DB : store user with bcrypt password hash
Auth -> Jwt : generateToken(amr=[pwd], mfa=false)
Jwt --> Auth : signed JWT
API -> Cookie : createAuthenticationCookie(jwt)
Cookie --> API : Set-Cookie header
Auth --> API : AuthResponse(..., token omitted from body)
API --> Browser : 201 Created + HttpOnly auth cookie

Student -> Browser : later enters email + password
Browser -> API : POST /api/auth/login over HTTPS
API -> Auth : login(credentials)
Auth -> DB : load user by email
DB --> Auth : user with bcrypt password hash
Auth -> Auth : verify with BCryptPasswordEncoder

alt MFA disabled for this account
  Auth -> Jwt : generateToken(amr=[pwd], mfa=false)
  Jwt --> Auth : signed JWT
  API -> Cookie : createAuthenticationCookie(jwt)
  Cookie --> API : Set-Cookie header
  Auth --> API : AuthResponse(authStatus=AUTHENTICATED)
  API --> Browser : 200 OK + HttpOnly auth cookie
else MFA enabled for this account
  Auth -> MFA : createChallenge(user)
  MFA -> DB : store short-lived MFA challenge
  DB --> MFA : challengeId + expiry + attempts
  MFA --> Auth : challenge details
  API -> Cookie : clearAuthenticationCookie()
  Cookie --> API : clearing Set-Cookie header
  Auth --> API : AuthResponse(authStatus=MFA_REQUIRED, challengeId)
  API --> Browser : 200 OK + MFA challenge metadata

  Student -> Browser : enter authenticator or recovery code
  Browser -> API : POST /api/auth/mfa/verify over HTTPS
  API -> MFA : verify(challengeId, verificationCode)
  MFA -> DB : load challenge + user MFA secret/recovery data
  DB --> MFA : pending challenge + protected MFA state
  MFA -> MFA : validate TOTP or consume recovery code
  MFA -> Jwt : generateToken(amr=[pwd, otp], mfa=true)
  Jwt --> MFA : signed JWT
  API -> Cookie : createAuthenticationCookie(jwt)
  Cookie --> API : Set-Cookie header
  MFA --> API : AuthResponse(authStatus=AUTHENTICATED)
  API --> Browser : 200 OK + HttpOnly auth cookie
end

Browser -> API : GET /api/auth/me with credentialed cookie request
API -> Cookie : extractToken(request cookies)
Cookie --> API : JWT from auth cookie
API -> Jwt : extract username and validate token
Jwt --> API : valid subject + claims
API -> DB : load current user
DB --> API : user profile + roles
API --> Browser : CurrentUserResponse

note right of Auth
Plaintext passwords are not stored.
Only the bcrypt password hash is verified.
end note

note right of MFA
No authenticated session cookie is established
before second-factor success.
TOTP secrets are protected at rest and
recovery codes are one-time backup credentials.
end note

note right of Jwt
JWT supports stateless session validation,
but it is not a data-encryption mechanism.
end note

note over Browser,API
The browser-facing contract is now cookie-based:
- JWT is transported in an HttpOnly auth cookie
- frontend code sends credentialed requests
- response bodies omit the raw token value
Auth API failures use a shared structured envelope for
validation, malformed-body, and auth-domain errors.
end note
@enduml

